# Design Documentation

## Location

- UX flows: `docs/design/domains/<domain>/ia-and-flows.md`
- Content and voice: `docs/design/domains/<domain>/content-and-voice.md`
- Domain overview: `docs/design/domains/<domain>/README.md`

## Required Content

Design documentation must include:

- **Flows**: User journey maps, interaction flows, state transitions
- **States**: All UI states (loading, error, empty, success, etc.)
- **Accessibility**: WCAG compliance, keyboard navigation, screen reader support
- **Content/Voice**: Messaging guidelines, tone, terminology
- **Components**: Design system components used (link to component library)

## Update Triggers

Update design docs when:
- UX flow changes (user journey, interaction patterns)
- UI states change (new states, removed states, state transitions)
- Interaction rules change (keyboard shortcuts, gestures, behaviors)
- Copy/voice changes (messaging, terminology, tone)
- Accessibility requirements change

## Linking Requirements

- Link to product requirements: `docs/product/domains/<domain>/requirements/<feature>.md`
- Link to technical implementation: `docs/tech/domains/<domain>/architecture.md`
- Reference shared services that affect UX: `docs/shared-services/<service>/README.md`
